    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Refers to the style and culture of the Anishininew, an indigenous people of Canada whose lands span from the provinces of Ontario to Manitoba. In the past, the Anishininew were named "Oji-Cree," referring to people whose culture and language result from a blend of Anishinaabe and Cree. However, the Anishininew consider themselves uniquely separate from both. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
